  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;All new external facing and roofing materials in respect of all the works hereby approved shall match those of the existing building in respect of materials used, detailed execution and finished appearance. Unless otherwise shown on the hereby approved plans.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\n\r\nREASON: In order to preserve the appearance of the host building, wider terrace, streetscene, and De Beauvoir Conservation Area.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "<p>The Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-96b1155a-7fff-cb6d-c583-eb3d79b00337&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;Prior to the commencement of the relevant part of works, detailed specification including a drainage layout and a management &amp;amp; maintenance plan (where applicable) of the permeable paving shall be submitted to, and approved by the LPA, in consultation with the LLFA. It must be demonstrated that there will be no increase in surface water flow being discharged offsite and an overall reduction in peak flow rate and volume.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-96b1155a-7fff-cb6d-c583-eb3d79b00337&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-96b1155a-7fff-cb6d-c583-eb3d79b00337&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;REASON: To ensure the proposed permeable paving reduces surface water flood risk. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
